WEBVTT

00:00:55.975 --> 00:00:58.269
You don't like flying, do you?

00:00:59.312 --> 00:01:01.397
What gives you that idea?

00:01:03.482 --> 00:01:08.195
You wanna know the secret
to surviving air travel?

00:01:08.279 --> 00:01:11.282
After you get where you're going,
take off your shoes and socks.

00:01:11.365 --> 00:01:16.787
Then you walk around on the rug barefoot
and make fists with your toes.

00:01:16.871 --> 00:01:19.081
Fists with your toes?

00:01:19.832 --> 00:01:24.003
I know. It sounds crazy. Trust me.
I've been doing it for nine years.

00:01:24.086 --> 00:01:28.257
Yes, sir! Better than a shower
and a hot cup of coffee.

00:01:28.341 --> 00:01:29.300
OK.

00:01:39.435 --> 00:01:41.562
It's OK. I'm a cop.

00:01:43.481 --> 00:01:47.318
Trust me. I've been doing this for 11 years.

00:01:47.610 --> 00:01:52.490
<i>(stewardess) The captain and the crew
would like to welcome you to Los Angeles.</i>

00:01:52.573 --> 00:01:55.951
<i>Have a very merry Christmas.</i>

00:02:03.918 --> 00:02:07.963
<i>(PA) Flight 247 to Tucson
now boarding at gate 14.</i>

00:02:09.757 --> 00:02:14.512
<i>Flight 247 to Tucson
now boarding at gate 14.</i>

00:02:21.602 --> 00:02:23.979
<i>(chamber music)</i>

00:02:27.441 --> 00:02:29.527
<i>(speak Japanese)</i>

00:02:43.249 --> 00:02:44.959
Ladies and gentlemen...

00:02:45.042 --> 00:02:47.336
Ladies and gentlemen!

00:02:47.420 --> 00:02:51.841
I want to congratulate all of you for
making this one of the greatest years

00:02:51.966 --> 00:02:54.510
in the history of the Nakatomi Corporation.

00:02:54.593 --> 00:02:56.679
<i>(applause and cheering)</i>

00:02:58.222 --> 00:03:01.225
On behalf of the Chief
Executive Officer, Mr Ozu,

00:03:01.308 --> 00:03:03.477
and the Board of Directors,

00:03:03.561 --> 00:03:07.773
we thank you one and all and wish you
a merry Christmas and a happy New Year!

00:03:07.857 --> 00:03:11.026
<i>(crowd)</i> Merry Christmas! Happy New Year!

00:03:12.027 --> 00:03:15.531
Hey, Holly. What about dinner tonight?

00:03:15.614 --> 00:03:18.242
Harry, it's Christmas Eve.

00:03:18.325 --> 00:03:21.370
Families, stockings...

00:03:22.496 --> 00:03:24.582
Chestnuts?

00:03:24.665 --> 00:03:28.753
Rudolph and Frosty?
Any of these things ring a bell?

00:03:28.836 --> 00:03:33.758
Actually, I was thinking more of
mulled wine, a nice aged Brie,

00:03:33.841 --> 00:03:38.387
and a roaring fireplace.
You know what I'm saying?

00:03:40.306 --> 00:03:43.642
Ginny, it's 5:40. Go join the party.
Have some champagne.

00:03:43.726 --> 00:03:46.353
You're making me feel
like Ebenezer Scrooge.

00:03:46.437 --> 00:03:50.149
Thanks. Do you think the baby
can handle a little sip?

00:03:50.232 --> 00:03:53.319
That baby's ready to tend bar.

00:03:53.903 --> 00:03:54.779
Last chance.

00:03:54.862 --> 00:03:56.739
Bye.

00:03:57.990 --> 00:03:59.867
<i>(phone rings)</i>

00:04:02.703 --> 00:04:05.706
McClane residence.
Lucy McClane speaking.

00:04:05.790 --> 00:04:10.211
Hello, Lucy McClane.
This is your mother speaking.

00:04:10.294 --> 00:04:13.255
<i>Mommy! When are you coming home?</i>

00:04:13.339 --> 00:04:17.301
Pretty soon. You'll be in bed
when I get there, though.

00:04:17.384 --> 00:04:19.887
Let me talk to Paulina, OK, hon?

00:04:19.970 --> 00:04:24.308
And no snooping around the house
looking for presents.

00:04:24.391 --> 00:04:26.894
Is Daddy coming home with you?

00:04:28.979 --> 00:04:33.484
Well, we'll see what Santa
and Mommy can do, OK?

00:04:33.567 --> 00:04:35.694
Put Paulina on. Bye, honey.

00:04:35.778 --> 00:04:37.279
<i>Paulina!</i>

00:04:42.409 --> 00:04:44.286
<i>Hola,</i> Mrs Holly.

00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:47.248
Um, did Mr McClane call?

00:04:47.331 --> 00:04:49.959
<i>No, Mrs Holly. No telefono.</i>

00:04:50.960 --> 00:04:54.046
He probably didn't have time
before his flight.

00:04:54.129 --> 00:04:58.092
It might be a good idea to make up
the spare bedroom, just in case.

00:04:58.175 --> 00:05:01.178
<i>Sí,</i> Mrs Holly. I do that already.

00:05:01.262 --> 00:05:04.390
What would I do without you, Paulina?

00:05:24.451 --> 00:05:26.537
<i>(woman squeals)</i>

00:05:29.790 --> 00:05:30.958
California!

00:05:44.054 --> 00:05:46.140
Hey, I'm John McClane.

00:05:46.223 --> 00:05:48.809
Argyle. I'm your limo driver.

00:05:52.021 --> 00:05:54.148
Nice bear.

00:05:57.735 --> 00:06:01.739
OK... Argyle. What do we do now?

00:06:01.822 --> 00:06:06.660
I was, uh, hoping you could tell me.
It's my first time driving a limo.

00:06:06.744 --> 00:06:09.663
That's OK. It's my first time riding in one.

00:06:09.997 --> 00:06:12.583
Relax. We got everything in this mug, man.

00:06:12.666 --> 00:06:15.920
Look at this - CD, CB, TV,

00:06:16.003 --> 00:06:18.505
telephone, full bar, VHS.

00:06:20.299 --> 00:06:24.845
If your friend's hot to trot, I know
a few mama bears we can hook up with.

00:06:26.180 --> 00:06:29.058
- Or is he married?
- He's married.

00:06:29.141 --> 00:06:30.184
OK.

00:06:31.852 --> 00:06:35.147
Oh, sorry about that. It's the girl's day off.

00:06:35.230 --> 00:06:37.566
I didn't know you were gonna sit up front.

00:06:37.650 --> 00:06:39.610
Your lady live out here?

00:06:39.693 --> 00:06:42.112
About the past six months.

00:06:42.196 --> 00:06:44.448
Meaning you still live in New York?

00:06:45.240 --> 00:06:48.452
You always ask this many questions, Argyle?

00:06:48.535 --> 00:06:53.123
Sorry. I used to drive a cab
and people would expect a little chitchat.

00:06:53.207 --> 00:06:56.502
- So, you divorced?
- Just drive the car, man.

00:06:56.585 --> 00:07:00.422
Hey, come on. You divorced?
You separated? She beat you up?!

00:07:03.342 --> 00:07:07.471
She had a good job.
It turned into a great career.

00:07:07.554 --> 00:07:12.476
- That meant she had to move here.
- You're very fast, Argyle.

00:07:12.559 --> 00:07:15.229
So, why didn't you come?

00:07:17.898 --> 00:07:21.360
Well? Why didn't you come with her?
What's up?

00:07:21.443 --> 00:07:23.278
Because I'm a New York cop.

00:07:23.362 --> 00:07:27.074
I got a backlog of scumbags
I'm still trying to put behind bars.

00:07:27.157 --> 00:07:29.159
I can't just go that easy.

00:07:29.243 --> 00:07:31.745
You thought she wasn't
gonna make it out here,

00:07:31.829 --> 00:07:36.166
and she'd come crawling back to you
so why bother to pack, right?

00:07:36.250 --> 00:07:39.336
Like I said, you're very fast, Argyle.

00:07:39.420 --> 00:07:41.422
Mind if we hear some tunes?

00:07:42.506 --> 00:07:44.508
<i>(♪ "Christmas in Hollis" by Run DMC)</i>

00:07:44.591 --> 00:07:46.802
Hey, that'll work.

00:07:49.430 --> 00:07:50.764
No Christmas music?

00:07:51.098 --> 00:07:53.642
This <i>is</i> Christmas music.

00:07:55.185 --> 00:07:57.604
<i>♪ It was December 24th
on Hollis Ave after dark</i>

00:07:57.688 --> 00:08:00.232
<i>♪ When I seen the man chillin'
with his dog in the park</i>

00:08:00.315 --> 00:08:02.735
<i>♪ I approached them very slowly
with my heart full of fear</i>

00:08:02.818 --> 00:08:05.529
<i>♪ Looked at his dog...
oh, my God, a ill reindeer</i>

00:08:05.612 --> 00:08:07.740
<i>♪ But then I was illin'
cos the man had a beard</i>

00:08:07.823 --> 00:08:10.367
<i>♪ And a bag full of goodies.
12 o'clock hit, man</i>

00:08:10.451 --> 00:08:12.703
<i>♪ So I turned my head a second,
and the man was gone</i>

00:08:12.786 --> 00:08:15.122
<i>♪ But he must have dropped his wallet
smack dead on the lawn</i>

00:08:15.205 --> 00:08:17.791
<i>♪ I picked the wallet up,
and then I took a pause</i>

00:08:17.875 --> 00:08:20.544
<i>♪ Took out the licence,
and it cold said Santa Claus</i>

00:08:20.627 --> 00:08:22.755
<i>♪ A million dollars in it,
cold hundreds and Gs</i>

00:08:22.838 --> 00:08:25.424
So your lady sees you,
you run into her arms,

00:08:25.507 --> 00:08:29.178
the music comes up
and you live happily ever after, right?

00:08:29.261 --> 00:08:32.056
I can live with that.

00:08:32.139 --> 00:08:35.976
So, if it doesn't work out,
you got a place to stay?

00:08:36.060 --> 00:08:38.729
I'll find a place.

00:08:38.812 --> 00:08:44.234
I tell you what. I'll wait in the garage.
You score, give me a call on the car phone.

00:08:44.318 --> 00:08:49.156
I'll take your bags to the desk.
You strike out, I'll get you a hotel.

00:08:49.239 --> 00:08:53.786
- You're all right, Argyle.
- Remember that when you sign for the tip.

00:09:17.351 --> 00:09:19.603
- Hi.
- Good evening.

00:09:19.686 --> 00:09:21.647
I'm here to see Holly McClane.

00:09:21.730 --> 00:09:23.899
Just type it in there.

00:09:30.030 --> 00:09:31.198
Cute toy.

00:09:31.281 --> 00:09:35.869
Yeah, if you have to take a leak,
it'll even help you find your zipper.

00:09:51.343 --> 00:09:53.387
Christ!

00:09:58.433 --> 00:10:00.561
- 30th floor?
- The party.

00:10:00.644 --> 00:10:02.646
They're the only ones left.

00:10:02.729 --> 00:10:06.483
Take the express elevator.
Get off where you hear the noise.

00:10:06.567 --> 00:10:08.068
Thanks.

00:10:11.655 --> 00:10:13.824
<i>(whistles "Jingle Bells")</i>

00:11:06.251 --> 00:11:08.754
- Champagne, sir?
- Yeah, thanks.

00:11:43.163 --> 00:11:45.082
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:11:45.666 --> 00:11:48.168
Hey! Merry Christmas!

00:11:51.838 --> 00:11:53.590
Jesus.

00:11:54.216 --> 00:11:55.801
Fuckin' California!

00:11:55.884 --> 00:11:58.011
<i>(woman)</i>
I couldn't agree with you more.

00:11:58.345 --> 00:12:00.305
Why don't I talk to him right now?

00:12:01.181 --> 00:12:03.809
Hi. I'm looking for...

00:12:03.892 --> 00:12:05.269
- Holly Gennero.
- Yeah.

00:12:05.352 --> 00:12:07.312
Then you must be John McClane.

00:12:07.396 --> 00:12:09.773
Joe Takagi. How was your ride in?

00:12:09.856 --> 00:12:12.359
Nice. I have you to thank for that?

00:12:12.442 --> 00:12:14.486
Seemed the least we could do.

00:12:14.569 --> 00:12:18.448
- Quite a place you have here.
- It will be if we ever get it finished.

00:12:18.532 --> 00:12:20.534
Still several floors under construction.

00:12:20.617 --> 00:12:24.413
Holly went to fax some documents.
She should be back any minute.

00:12:24.496 --> 00:12:27.708
In the meanwhile, her office is back here.

00:12:30.002 --> 00:12:31.003
Ellis?

00:12:32.212 --> 00:12:35.966
<i>(sniffing)</i> I was making a call.
This was the nearest phone.

00:12:36.049 --> 00:12:38.635
I want you to meet John McClane,

00:12:38.719 --> 00:12:40.762
Holly's husband.

00:12:40.846 --> 00:12:42.723
Holly's policeman.

00:12:42.806 --> 00:12:45.142
Ellis is in charge
of international development.

00:12:45.225 --> 00:12:47.436
Heard a lot about you.

00:12:47.519 --> 00:12:49.313
You missed some.

00:12:49.396 --> 00:12:50.814
<i>(Ellis sniffs)</i>

00:12:50.897 --> 00:12:52.607
Can I get you anything?

00:12:52.691 --> 00:12:55.736
Food? Cake?
Some watered-down champagne?

00:12:55.819 --> 00:12:57.904
No, thank you. I'm fine.

00:12:59.364 --> 00:13:01.575
You throw quite a party.

00:13:02.576 --> 00:13:05.495
I didn't realise they celebrated
Christmas in Japan.

00:13:05.579 --> 00:13:09.708
We're flexible. Pearl Harbor didn't work out,
so we got you with tape decks.

00:13:09.791 --> 00:13:12.377
<i>(exaggerated laugh)</i>

00:13:12.461 --> 00:13:17.758
It's a double celebration. We closed
a big deal today, mainly due to Holly.

00:13:19.009 --> 00:13:21.595
I'll be out in a couple of minutes.

00:13:25.766 --> 00:13:27.100
John.

00:13:31.271 --> 00:13:35.233
- Have you met everyone?
- We've been sticking him with spears!

00:13:35.317 --> 00:13:37.903
Of course he has.

00:13:37.986 --> 00:13:41.156
She was made for the business.
Tough as nails.

00:13:41.239 --> 00:13:43.950
I was hoping you made that flight.

00:13:44.034 --> 00:13:46.203
Show him the watch.

00:13:46.787 --> 00:13:48.246
Later.

00:13:48.330 --> 00:13:52.250
Show him. Are you embarrassed?
It's a token of appreciation

00:13:52.334 --> 00:13:55.754
for all her hard work. It's a Rolex.

00:13:55.837 --> 00:13:58.340
I'm sure I'll see it later.

00:13:58.423 --> 00:14:01.426
Is there a place where I could wash up?

00:14:01.510 --> 00:14:02.969
Sure.

00:14:18.568 --> 00:14:22.906
You have to forgive Ellis.
He gets very depressed this time of year.

00:14:22.989 --> 00:14:26.243
He thought <i>he</i> was
God's greatest gift, you know?

00:14:26.326 --> 00:14:28.620
I know the type.

00:14:28.703 --> 00:14:31.748
I think he's got his eye on you.

00:14:31.832 --> 00:14:35.669
That's OK. I have my eye
on his private bathroom.

00:14:35.752 --> 00:14:38.839
Where are you staying?
Things happened so fast

00:14:38.922 --> 00:14:41.675
I didn't get a chance
to ask you on the phone.

00:14:41.758 --> 00:14:44.261
Cappy Roberts retired out here.

00:14:44.970 --> 00:14:49.599
- He said I could bunk with him.
- Cappy retired, huh? Where's he live?

00:14:49.683 --> 00:14:52.894
- Romona.
- Ha! Pomona.

00:14:53.228 --> 00:14:55.564
- Huh?
- Pomona.

00:14:55.689 --> 00:14:57.524
- Pomona.
- Yeah.

00:14:58.442 --> 00:15:00.777
You'll be in the car half the time.

00:15:02.237 --> 00:15:05.782
Why don't we make it easy?
I have a spare bedroom.

00:15:05.866 --> 00:15:08.493
It's not huge or anything, but...

00:15:08.577 --> 00:15:12.038
the kids would love
to have you at the house.

00:15:13.248 --> 00:15:16.168
They would, huh?

00:15:18.128 --> 00:15:20.422
I would, too.

00:15:20.839 --> 00:15:23.550
<i>(woman)</i> Ooh!

00:15:23.633 --> 00:15:25.051
Sorry.

00:15:31.975 --> 00:15:34.561
I missed you.

00:15:40.942 --> 00:15:43.820
Didn't miss my name, though, huh?

00:15:43.904 --> 00:15:47.115
Except maybe when you're signing cheques?

00:15:47.199 --> 00:15:50.076
Since when did you start using Ms Gennero?

00:15:52.245 --> 00:15:56.166
This is a Japanese company.
They figure a married woman's...

00:15:56.249 --> 00:15:58.335
You <i>are</i> a married woman.

00:15:58.418 --> 00:16:03.173
- This conversation again?
- We never finished this conversation.

00:16:03.256 --> 00:16:08.512
- I had an opportunity. I had to take it.
- No matter what it did to our marriage.

00:16:08.595 --> 00:16:12.724
- It changed your idea of our marriage.
- You have no clue what my idea...

00:16:12.807 --> 00:16:16.394
I know exactly what your idea
of our marriage should be.

00:16:16.478 --> 00:16:18.271
<i>(knocking)</i> Ms Gennero, I...

00:16:19.981 --> 00:16:21.691
Excuse me.

00:16:22.275 --> 00:16:23.568
Hi.

00:16:24.861 --> 00:16:29.574
Mr Takagi is looking for you.
He wants you to say something to the troops.

00:16:29.658 --> 00:16:30.450
Thank you.

00:16:35.121 --> 00:16:36.957
Speech time.

00:16:37.040 --> 00:16:39.543
Be back in a few minutes.

00:16:50.762 --> 00:16:52.389
That was great, John.

00:16:52.472 --> 00:16:55.475
Good job. Very mature.

00:17:45.191 --> 00:17:50.238
So Kareem rebounds. Feeds Worthy
on the break, over to AC, to Magic,

00:17:50.322 --> 00:17:52.866
then back to Worthy.

00:17:52.949 --> 00:17:54.784
Boom! Two points.

00:17:59.581 --> 00:18:00.206
We're in.

00:18:13.219 --> 00:18:14.763
<i>(hums)</i>

00:20:11.337 --> 00:20:12.505
<i>(beep)</i>

00:20:29.689 --> 00:20:30.940
<i>Links...</i>

00:20:33.902 --> 00:20:34.986
<i>rechts,</i>

00:20:35.069 --> 00:20:36.863
<i>und wieder links.</i>

00:21:07.393 --> 00:21:08.978
Son of a bitch.

00:21:12.190 --> 00:21:14.359
Fists with your toes.

00:21:45.640 --> 00:21:47.183
Yeah, Argyle?

00:21:47.267 --> 00:21:48.768
<i>How's it going?</i>

00:21:48.852 --> 00:21:50.103
OK. Where are you?

00:21:50.186 --> 00:21:53.147
At the garage.
What's with you and your lady?

00:21:54.107 --> 00:21:55.525
The vote's not in yet.

00:22:03.992 --> 00:22:07.245
<i>- He, Bruder.
- Moment.</i>

00:22:07.328 --> 00:22:08.788
<i>Nein! Nein! Nein!</i>

00:22:08.872 --> 00:22:10.707
<i>Warte doch. Nicht!</i>

00:22:27.390 --> 00:22:28.433
Argyle?

00:22:29.058 --> 00:22:31.144
Mac, you there? Hello?

00:22:39.736 --> 00:22:41.821
You know the number. Use it.

00:23:06.971 --> 00:23:08.389
<i>(machine-gun fire)</i>

00:23:08.723 --> 00:23:09.849
<i>(screaming)</i>

00:23:11.351 --> 00:23:13.436
<i>(machine-gun fire)</i>

00:23:30.370 --> 00:23:32.246
<i>(woman screams)</i>

00:23:50.723 --> 00:23:52.642
<i>(speaks German)</i>

00:24:07.740 --> 00:24:09.534
<i>(crowd screams)</i>

00:24:09.617 --> 00:24:11.869
<i>(machine-gun fire)</i>

00:24:14.038 --> 00:24:16.916
Stay calm. Everything's going to be fine.

00:24:17.000 --> 00:24:18.876
Everything's going to be fine.

00:24:38.271 --> 00:24:39.647
Shit!

00:24:42.942 --> 00:24:44.110
Think.

00:24:44.569 --> 00:24:46.070
Think.

00:24:53.453 --> 00:24:55.246
<i>(crowd screams)</i>

00:25:01.961 --> 00:25:05.214
Ladies and gentlemen.

00:25:06.049 --> 00:25:07.633
Ladies and gentlemen.

00:25:07.717 --> 00:25:09.677
<i>(crowd quietens)</i>

00:25:14.974 --> 00:25:19.270
Due to the Nakatomi Corporation's
legacy of greed around the globe,

00:25:19.353 --> 00:25:24.567
they're about to be taught a lesson
in the <i>real</i> use of power.

00:25:24.650 --> 00:25:26.861
You will be witnesses.

00:25:29.072 --> 00:25:30.073
Now,

00:25:31.157 --> 00:25:33.034
where is Mr Takagi?

00:25:35.661 --> 00:25:39.082
Joseph Yashinobo Takagi,

00:25:40.583 --> 00:25:42.543
born Kyoto, 1937.

00:25:42.627 --> 00:25:44.879
<i>(whispers)</i> Don't move.

00:25:44.962 --> 00:25:48.674
Family emigrated to San Pedro,
California, 1939,

00:25:50.134 --> 00:25:54.639
interned at Manzanar, 1942 to '43,

00:25:55.973 --> 00:25:59.644
scholarship student,
University of California,

00:26:00.228 --> 00:26:02.063
1955.

00:26:06.025 --> 00:26:10.613
Law degree, Stanford, 1962.

00:26:10.696 --> 00:26:13.991
MBA, Harvard, 1970.

00:26:15.618 --> 00:26:17.870
President, Nakatomi Trading.

00:26:17.954 --> 00:26:21.290
Vice Chairman, Nakatomi Investment Group...

00:26:21.374 --> 00:26:22.458
Enough.

00:26:23.584 --> 00:26:25.670
And father

00:26:25.753 --> 00:26:27.296
of five.

00:26:27.380 --> 00:26:30.341
I am Takagi.

00:26:30.424 --> 00:26:32.552
How do you do?

