and stay calm. This is simply the beginning.

00:58:53.532 --> 00:58:55.034
<i>(static)</i>

00:58:55.117 --> 00:58:58.579
I told you all I wanted radio silence until...

00:58:58.662 --> 00:59:01.373
I'm sorry, Hans. I didn't get that message.

00:59:01.457 --> 00:59:04.835
<i>Maybe you should have put it
on a bulletin board.</i>

00:59:04.919 --> 00:59:07.463
I figured since I waxed Tony,
Marco and his friend,

00:59:07.546 --> 00:59:12.384
you and Karl and Franco might be lonely
so I wanted to give you a call.

00:59:12.468 --> 00:59:16.013
<i>(Karl)</i> How does he know so much about us?

00:59:16.097 --> 00:59:18.599
That's very kind of you.

00:59:18.682 --> 00:59:22.269
<i>I assume you are
our mysterious party crasher.</i>

00:59:22.353 --> 00:59:25.940
You are troublesome
for a security guard.

00:59:26.023 --> 00:59:28.818
Eeeh! Sorry, Hans. Wrong guess.

00:59:28.901 --> 00:59:34.532
Would you like to go for double jeopardy
where the scores can really change?

00:59:36.826 --> 00:59:39.203
Mm, these are very bad for you.

00:59:40.079 --> 00:59:43.958
- Who are you, then?
- Just the fly in the ointment, Hans.

00:59:44.041 --> 00:59:47.461
The monkey in the wrench,
the pain in the ass.

00:59:50.172 --> 00:59:51.590
Whoa!

00:59:52.633 --> 00:59:55.094
Check on all the others. Don't use the radio.

00:59:55.177 --> 00:59:59.348
See if he's lying about Marco
and find out if anyone else is missing.

01:00:02.977 --> 01:00:05.062
Mr Mystery Guest...

01:00:06.147 --> 01:00:07.898
are you still there?

01:00:08.649 --> 01:00:13.112
Yeah, I'm still here, unless you
wanna open the front door for me.

01:00:13.195 --> 01:00:15.114
No, I'm afraid not,

01:00:15.197 --> 01:00:17.992
but you have me at a loss.

01:00:18.075 --> 01:00:19.827
You know my name, but who are you?

01:00:19.910 --> 01:00:24.081
<i>Just another American
who saw too many movies as a child?</i>

01:00:24.165 --> 01:00:27.334
<i>Another orphan of a bankrupt culture</i>

01:00:27.418 --> 01:00:31.755
<i>who thinks he's John Wayne,
Rambo, Marshal Dillon?</i>

01:00:31.839 --> 01:00:37.136
I was always partial to Roy Rogers, actually.
I liked those sequinned shirts.

01:00:37.219 --> 01:00:40.472
Do you really think you have
a chance against us, Mr Cowboy?

01:00:43.601 --> 01:00:45.936
Yippee-ki-yay, motherfucker.

01:00:49.690 --> 01:00:51.817
I'll beat everyone if I get a remote.

01:00:51.901 --> 01:00:53.694
<i>(man)</i> I don't have the new pages.

01:00:53.777 --> 01:00:56.030
Harvey, keep your pants on.

01:00:56.113 --> 01:00:57.865
Sam, I'm begging you.

01:00:57.948 --> 01:01:01.160
Simon's with the remote.
I'll tell him to swing by.

01:01:01.243 --> 01:01:03.078
I won't sit on this!

01:01:03.162 --> 01:01:05.956
This is my story! I'm going out there!

01:01:06.040 --> 01:01:09.960
Look, Sam. Tell you what.
You don't give me a truck, I'll steal a truck.

01:01:10.044 --> 01:01:12.463
<i>- (Harvey)</i> Give us a break, Thornburg.
- Eat it, Harvey!

01:01:12.546 --> 01:01:15.132
..four, three, two,

01:01:15.216 --> 01:01:16.550
one.

01:01:16.634 --> 01:01:18.969
Harvey, we're on the air.

01:01:22.681 --> 01:01:25.809
Good evening. This is Harvey Johnson.

01:01:26.644 --> 01:01:30.439
And I'm Gail Wallens.
This is <i>Nightline News at Ten.</i>

01:01:30.522 --> 01:01:33.317
Our top stories on this Christmas Eve...

01:01:33.400 --> 01:01:36.570
Take truck number five and get outta here.

01:01:44.370 --> 01:01:47.790
He wasn't lying about Marco.
He's down on the street.

01:01:47.873 --> 01:01:50.167
The other man was Heinrich,

01:01:50.251 --> 01:01:52.795
and his bag is missing.

01:01:54.296 --> 01:01:56.465
He had the detonator.

01:02:00.678 --> 01:02:02.263
Theo.

01:02:02.346 --> 01:02:03.389
<i>Theo.</i>

01:02:03.597 --> 01:02:05.015
Yo!

01:02:05.099 --> 01:02:08.769
<i>We may have some problems.
How's our schedule?</i>

01:02:08.852 --> 01:02:14.400
- Three down, four to go.
- Then don't waste time talking to me.

01:02:14.483 --> 01:02:17.444
This is Sergeant Al Powell
of the LA Police Department.

01:02:17.528 --> 01:02:22.574
If the person who radioed can hear me,
acknowledge this transmission.

01:02:22.658 --> 01:02:23.701
I say again,

01:02:23.784 --> 01:02:27.121
if the person who radioed
for help can hear me,

01:02:27.204 --> 01:02:29.665
acknowledge this transmission!

01:02:33.961 --> 01:02:36.588
I read you, pal. You the guy in the car?

01:02:36.672 --> 01:02:38.632
What's left of him.

01:02:38.716 --> 01:02:42.177
<i>- Can you identify yourself?</i>
- Not now. Maybe later.

01:02:42.261 --> 01:02:46.348
This is a party line.
The neighbours got itchy trigger fingers.

01:02:46.432 --> 01:02:49.893
Here's the deal. You got 30 or so
hostages on the 30th floor.

01:02:49.977 --> 01:02:51.395
<i>The leader's name is Hans.</i>

01:02:51.478 --> 01:02:54.148
We have to shut him up.
He's telling them everything!

01:02:54.231 --> 01:02:56.317
Let him. I'm waiting for the FBI.

01:02:56.400 --> 01:03:00.863
He can waste as much time as he likes
but we <i>must</i> find the bag.

01:03:00.946 --> 01:03:04.408
<i>- (McClane) They have a freakin' arsenal here.</i>
- We must have the detonators.

01:03:04.491 --> 01:03:09.580
<i>They got missiles and enough plastic
explosives to orbit Arnold Schwarzenegger.</i>

01:03:09.663 --> 01:03:12.499
They're down to nine,
counting the skydiver you met.

01:03:12.583 --> 01:03:17.921
These guys are mostly European,
judging by their clothing labels, and...

01:03:23.844 --> 01:03:25.387
cigarettes.

01:03:25.471 --> 01:03:28.015
They're well-financed and very slick.

01:03:28.098 --> 01:03:29.767
How do you know that?

01:03:29.850 --> 01:03:31.602
I've seen enough phoney IDs

01:03:31.685 --> 01:03:35.522
to recognise the ones they got
must have cost a fortune.

01:03:37.816 --> 01:03:40.235
Add all that up, I don't know what it means,

01:03:40.319 --> 01:03:43.906
but you got some bad-ass perpetrators
and they're here to stay.

01:03:45.491 --> 01:03:50.454
I hear you, partner. LA's finest are on it,
so light 'em if you got 'em.

01:03:50.537 --> 01:03:53.332
Way ahead of you, partner.

01:03:53.874 --> 01:03:56.001
<i>So what do I call you?</i>

01:03:57.544 --> 01:03:58.629
Call me...

01:04:00.506 --> 01:04:01.340
Roy.

01:04:01.423 --> 01:04:06.428
Listen up, Roy, if you think of anything else,
don't be shy, OK?

01:04:06.512 --> 01:04:10.474
In the meantime, find a safe place
and let us do our job. Understand?

01:04:10.557 --> 01:04:12.851
<i>(McClane) They're all yours, Al.</i>

01:04:30.327 --> 01:04:32.579
Who's talking to 'em?

01:04:32.663 --> 01:04:35.707
I am, sir. Sergeant Powell. Al Powell.

01:04:36.166 --> 01:04:40.212
Dwayne Robinson. What's the deal?
What do these pricks want?

01:04:40.295 --> 01:04:44.550
If you mean the terrorists,
we haven't heard from them.

01:04:44.633 --> 01:04:47.469
Who have you been talking to?

01:04:47.553 --> 01:04:50.431
We don't know. He won't give us his name.

01:04:50.514 --> 01:04:53.100
But he appears to be the one who phoned.

01:04:53.183 --> 01:04:56.478
He's killed one terrorist
and claims he capped off two others.

01:04:56.562 --> 01:04:58.605
He claims?

01:04:58.689 --> 01:05:02.526
Powell, has it occurred to you
he could be one of the terrorists,

01:05:02.609 --> 01:05:04.361
or some nutcase in there?

01:05:04.445 --> 01:05:07.531
I don't think so. In fact, I think he's a cop,

01:05:07.614 --> 01:05:10.409
maybe not LAPD,
but he's definitely a badge.

01:05:10.492 --> 01:05:13.745
- How do you know that?
- A hunch. Things he said -

01:05:13.829 --> 01:05:16.623
like being able to spot a phoney ID.

01:05:16.707 --> 01:05:18.792
Jesus Christ, Powell!

01:05:18.876 --> 01:05:21.378
He could be a bartender for all we know!

01:05:21.462 --> 01:05:23.839
TV's here.

01:05:23.922 --> 01:05:25.549
Oh, shit.

01:05:25.632 --> 01:05:27.301
<i>(horns blare)</i>

01:05:42.566 --> 01:05:46.487
- I have a request.
- What idiot put you in charge?

01:05:46.570 --> 01:05:48.530
You did...

01:05:48.614 --> 01:05:53.785
when you murdered my boss.
Now everybody's looking to me.

01:05:53.869 --> 01:05:58.999
Personally, I'd pass on the job.
I don't enjoy being this close to you.

01:06:06.965 --> 01:06:08.300
Go on.

01:06:08.383 --> 01:06:10.344
We have a pregnant woman.

01:06:10.427 --> 01:06:13.347
Relax. She's not due for a couple of weeks,

01:06:13.430 --> 01:06:16.600
but sitting on that rock
isn't doing her back any good.

01:06:16.683 --> 01:06:21.855
So I would like permission to move her
to an office with a sofa.

01:06:21.939 --> 01:06:24.858
No, but I'll have a sofa
brought out. Good enough?

01:06:24.942 --> 01:06:26.735
Good enough.

01:06:26.818 --> 01:06:32.491
And unless you like it messy, I'd start
bringing us in groups to the bathroom.

01:06:32.574 --> 01:06:36.161
Yes. You're right. It will be done.

01:06:36.828 --> 01:06:40.207
Was there something else?

01:06:40.290 --> 01:06:42.292
No, thank you.

01:06:48.340 --> 01:06:52.010
Mr Takagi chose his people well, Mrs...?

01:06:52.094 --> 01:06:54.221
Gennero.

01:06:55.138 --> 01:06:57.474
<i>Ms</i> Gennero.

01:07:00.102 --> 01:07:02.688
<i>(TV) We interrupt this programme
for a special bulletin.</i>

01:07:02.771 --> 01:07:06.650
<i>This is Richard Thornburg
live from Century City.</i>

01:07:06.733 --> 01:07:11.989
<i>Tonight, Los Angeles has joined
the sad and worldwide fraternity of cities</i>

01:07:12.072 --> 01:07:14.074
<i>whose only membership requirement</i>

01:07:14.157 --> 01:07:17.244
<i>is to suffer the anguish
of international terrorism.</i>

01:07:17.327 --> 01:07:21.707
<i>Approximately two hours ago,
an unidentified group of men</i>

01:07:21.790 --> 01:07:26.795
<i>seized control of the Nakatomi building,
sealing off all entrances and exits.</i>

01:07:26.878 --> 01:07:31.174
<i>All telephone lines have been cut
and the only communication now possible</i>

01:07:31.258 --> 01:07:34.177
<i>has been through the use
of CB communicators</i>

01:07:34.261 --> 01:07:36.638
<i>which the group brought with them.</i>

01:07:36.722 --> 01:07:41.226
<i>According to official sources,
the perpetrators of this building siege...</i>

01:07:41.310 --> 01:07:43.979
<i>(officer) Unit five, hold your position.</i>

01:07:44.313 --> 01:07:48.358
<i>(man)</i> We got Charlie unit in position
by the parking structure.

01:07:48.442 --> 01:07:52.487
<i>(Robinson)</i> Let me ask you... does
this stairway go up to the escalator?

01:07:52.571 --> 01:07:55.616
- Yeah.
- Tell them to go ahead.

01:07:56.325 --> 01:07:58.660
What's going on?

01:07:58.744 --> 01:08:00.912
What's it look like? We're going in.

01:08:00.996 --> 01:08:05.834
Going in? That's crazy! There could be
over 30 hostages in there for all we know.

01:08:05.917 --> 01:08:07.836
We don't know shit, Powell.

01:08:07.919 --> 01:08:11.298
If there's hostages, how come
there are no ransom demands?

01:08:11.381 --> 01:08:14.676
If there's terrorists in there,
where's their list of demands?

01:08:14.760 --> 01:08:16.970
All we know is that
somebody shot your car up.

01:08:17.054 --> 01:08:21.350
It's probably the same silly son of a bitch
you've been talking to on that radio.

01:08:21.433 --> 01:08:23.060
Excuse me, sir,

01:08:23.185 --> 01:08:26.438
but what about the body
that fell out the window?

01:08:26.521 --> 01:08:29.566
- Maybe a stockbroker got depressed.
- We're ready.

01:08:29.650 --> 01:08:31.985
- Light 'em up. Let's go.
- Hit your lights.

01:08:32.069 --> 01:08:34.988
- Blue units, go.
- Lights on!

01:08:46.917 --> 01:08:49.169
Powell?

01:08:49.252 --> 01:08:51.963
Powell, you still with me, babe?
What's going on?

01:08:52.673 --> 01:08:54.007
Yo, Al.

01:08:54.091 --> 01:08:57.844
I'm here, Roy, but I'm busy right now.
I'll talk to you later.

01:08:57.928 --> 01:09:00.639
- Al, what's wrong?
<i>- I'll talk to you later.</i>

01:09:00.722 --> 01:09:05.894
If you are what I think you are,
you'll know when to listen, shut up, and...

01:09:06.895 --> 01:09:08.855
and when to pray.

01:09:08.939 --> 01:09:11.149
Jesus Christ! You're coming in, right?

01:09:12.317 --> 01:09:14.736
I told you what kind
of people you're dealing with!

01:09:14.820 --> 01:09:17.114
<i>(Robinson)</i> Let's load them up.

01:09:20.534 --> 01:09:22.994
They'll be coming. Everyone get ready.

01:09:23.912 --> 01:09:26.540
<i>Theo, you are the eyes now.</i>

01:09:39.010 --> 01:09:40.303
- Rivers.
<i>- Yo.</i>

01:09:40.387 --> 01:09:43.181
Begin your reconnoitre.

01:09:43.807 --> 01:09:45.183
Let's go.

01:09:48.395 --> 01:09:49.980
Shit!

01:10:08.915 --> 01:10:11.168
Come on. Let's go.

01:10:21.178 --> 01:10:22.888
Ow! Jesus!

01:10:52.542 --> 01:10:54.544
<i>(tyres squeal)</i>

01:10:56.963 --> 01:10:59.382
All right, spread out.

01:11:03.345 --> 01:11:05.013
<i>(hums)</i>

01:11:25.242 --> 01:11:27.202
Shut up.

01:11:28.703 --> 01:11:30.580
Let's go.

01:11:35.210 --> 01:11:37.128
You macho assholes. No! No!

01:11:40.090 --> 01:11:41.842
Ahem... all right.

01:11:41.925 --> 01:11:43.927
Listen up, guys.

01:11:45.303 --> 01:11:48.515
'Twas the night before Christmas,
and all through the house,

01:11:48.598 --> 01:11:51.059
not a creature was stirring, except

01:11:51.142 --> 01:11:55.981
the four assholes coming in the rear
in standard two-by-two cover formation.

01:11:58.400 --> 01:11:59.693
We're all set.

01:12:01.069 --> 01:12:03.029
We're ready.

01:12:03.113 --> 01:12:04.447
Kick ass.

01:12:04.531 --> 01:12:05.657
Go!

01:12:05.740 --> 01:12:07.909
Right. Let's do it.

01:12:23.383 --> 01:12:24.801
Take cover!

01:12:25.218 --> 01:12:26.720
They're shooting at 'em.

01:12:26.803 --> 01:12:30.807
- It's panic fire. They can't see anything.
- They're shooting at the lights.

01:12:35.103 --> 01:12:38.648
They're going after the lights. Call them back.

01:12:39.608 --> 01:12:41.026
It's not happening.

01:12:41.109 --> 01:12:42.319
Mike, burn it.

01:12:44.571 --> 01:12:47.032
Don't be impatient.

01:12:47.115 --> 01:12:49.284
<i>Just wound them.</i>

01:12:50.785 --> 01:12:55.332
- Get them back. They're sitting ducks.
- They're almost in.

01:12:55.457 --> 01:12:58.168
Send in the car. Send in the car.

01:13:11.640 --> 01:13:13.016
Jesus Christ!

01:13:16.144 --> 01:13:18.897
Rivers, Rodriguez, report.

01:13:18.980 --> 01:13:21.900
Wait a minute.
What have we here, gentlemen?

01:13:25.946 --> 01:13:28.615
The police have themselves an RV.

01:13:33.912 --> 01:13:35.246
Southeast corner.

01:13:37.374 --> 01:13:39.209
<i>(shouting in German)</i>

01:13:48.343 --> 01:13:50.220
Oh, Jesus Christ.

01:13:51.763 --> 01:13:53.890
<i>(elevator whirrs)</i>

01:14:02.148 --> 01:14:04.859
Get back! Get the fuck back!

01:14:06.653 --> 01:14:07.779
Get over there.

01:14:07.862 --> 01:14:09.280
<i>Schnell! Schnell!</i>

01:14:09.364 --> 01:14:11.491
<i>Mach schnell!</i>

01:14:14.369 --> 01:14:16.246
<i>Weiter! Weiter! Weiter!</i>

01:14:16.329 --> 01:14:18.206
<i>Mach schnell! Mach schnell!</i>

01:14:18.289 --> 01:14:19.457
<i>Weiter!</i>

01:14:22.460 --> 01:14:24.004
<i>Mach los! Mach los!</i>

01:14:43.982 --> 01:14:44.941
I see him!

01:14:51.197 --> 01:14:52.657
<i>(speaks German)</i>

01:14:56.578 --> 01:14:58.246
<i>- Feuer!</i>
- Clear!

01:15:04.252 --> 01:15:07.255
Oh, my God! The quarterback is toast!

01:15:07.839 --> 01:15:10.425
Hang on, Rivers. That's an order.

01:15:11.676 --> 01:15:12.635
Hit it again.

01:15:12.719 --> 01:15:15.972
All right, you made your point!
Let 'em pull back!

01:15:16.056 --> 01:15:18.558
Thank you. I'll take it under advisement.

01:15:19.267 --> 01:15:20.935
Hit it again.

01:15:34.407 --> 01:15:35.700
Fire.

01:15:50.256 --> 01:15:52.217
Fuck me.

01:15:52.300 --> 01:15:54.886
Get them out of the car! They're burning!

01:16:05.146 --> 01:16:05.772
Fuck it.

01:16:06.815 --> 01:16:08.525
<i>(speaks German)</i>

01:16:08.608 --> 01:16:10.276
<i>Mach schnell! Mach los!</i>

01:16:18.159 --> 01:16:21.788
Let's see you take this
under advisement, jerkweed.

01:16:25.500 --> 01:16:27.418
Geronimo, motherfucker.

01:16:46.187 --> 01:16:47.188
Oh, shit!

01:16:52.485 --> 01:16:56.739
- They're using artillery on us!
- You idiot, it's not the police.

01:16:56.823 --> 01:16:58.533
It's him.

01:17:06.040 --> 01:17:07.333
Holy shit.

01:17:12.672 --> 01:17:14.674
My God!

01:17:16.342 --> 01:17:19.262
- Tell me you got that.
- I got it.

01:17:20.680 --> 01:17:23.099
Eat your heart out, Channel 5.

01:17:23.224 --> 01:17:27.187
<i>(TV) We've had an update on the terrorist
takeover of the Nakatomi building.</i>

01:17:27.270 --> 01:17:31.524
<i>Sources say the terrorist leader, Hans,
may be this man, Hans Gruber.</i>

01:17:31.608 --> 01:17:34.527
<i>A member of the radical
West German Volksfrei movement.</i>

01:17:34.611 --> 01:17:38.406
<i>The Volksfrei leadership
issued a communiqué an hour ago,</i>

01:17:38.531 --> 01:17:41.284
<i>stating that Gruber had been
expelled from that organisation.</i>

01:17:41.367 --> 01:17:43.745
<i>(McClane) Al, do you copy?</i>

01:17:43.828 --> 01:17:46.080
Are you all right?

01:17:46.164 --> 01:17:47.540
Yeah, I'm fine.

01:17:47.624 --> 01:17:48.583
<i>(coughing)</i>

01:17:48.666 --> 01:17:50.001
W-what was that?

01:17:50.084 --> 01:17:53.004
<i>Remember that plastic
explosive I told you about?</i>

01:17:53.087 --> 01:17:56.007
There you go. Is the building on fire?

01:17:56.090 --> 01:17:59.594
No, but it's gonna need a paint job
and a shitload of screen doors.

01:17:59.677 --> 01:18:02.430
Our spotter said you got two with that blast.

01:18:02.513 --> 01:18:05.058
- Is that him?
- Yes, sir.

01:18:06.684 --> 01:18:09.354
I don't know who you think you are,

01:18:09.437 --> 01:18:11.898
but you just destroyed a building.

01:18:11.981 --> 01:18:15.068
<i>We do not want your help. Is that clear?</i>

01:18:15.151 --> 01:18:16.986
<i>We don't want your help.</i>

01:18:17.070 --> 01:18:20.156
<i>I've got 100 people down here
covered with glass.</i>

01:18:20.240 --> 01:18:24.202
Glass? Who gives a shit about glass?
Who the fuck is this?

01:18:25.828 --> 01:18:28.498
This is Deputy Chief of Police
Dwayne T Robinson,

01:18:28.581 --> 01:18:30.541
and I am in charge of this situation.

01:18:30.625 --> 01:18:32.418
Oh, you're in charge?

01:18:32.502 --> 01:18:34.504
I got some bad news for you, Dwayne.

01:18:34.587 --> 01:18:37.882
<i>From up here it doesn't look
like you're in charge of shit.</i>

01:18:37.966 --> 01:18:40.051
Listen to me, you little asshole...

01:18:40.134 --> 01:18:41.010
<i>Asshole?</i>

01:18:41.094 --> 01:18:44.806
I'm not the one who just got buttfucked
on national TV, Dwayne.

01:18:44.889 --> 01:18:46.140
Ah-ha-ha!

01:18:46.224 --> 01:18:48.017
<i>Listen to me, jerk-off,</i>

01:18:48.101 --> 01:18:51.104
<i>if you're not part of the solution,
you're part of the problem.</i>

01:18:51.187 --> 01:18:55.191
<i>Quit being part of the problem
and put the other guy back on!</i>

01:18:57.193 --> 01:18:58.903
Hey, Roy, how you feeling?

01:18:58.987 --> 01:19:00.989
Pretty fucking unappreciated, Al.

01:19:01.072 --> 01:19:03.324
<i>Hey, look. I love you.</i>

01:19:03.408 --> 01:19:05.618
<i>So do a lot of the other guys.</i>

01:19:05.702 --> 01:19:08.329
So hang in there, man, you hear me?

01:19:08.413 --> 01:19:10.331
You hang in there.

01:19:11.916 --> 01:19:14.377
Yeah, thanks, partner.

01:19:14.961 --> 01:19:16.796
<i>(Ellis snorts)</i>

01:19:20.300 --> 01:19:21.676
What are you doing?

01:19:21.759 --> 01:19:25.555
I'm tired of sitting here waiting to see
who gets us killed first,

01:19:25.638 --> 01:19:27.140
them or your husband.

01:19:27.223 --> 01:19:28.808
What are you going to do?

01:19:28.891 --> 01:19:34.314
I negotiate million-dollar deals for breakfast.
I think I can handle this Euro trash.

01:19:34.397 --> 01:19:37.275
Hey, <i>sprechen sie</i> talk, huh?

01:19:37.358 --> 01:19:40.236
If you'd listened to me,
he would be neutralised already.

01:19:40.320 --> 01:19:43.239
- I don't want neutral. I want dead.
<i>- (knocking)</i>

01:19:43.448 --> 01:19:46.492
- Hope I'm not interrupting.
- What does he want?

01:19:46.576 --> 01:19:50.246
It's not what I want. It's what I can give you.

01:19:57.670 --> 01:20:00.006
Look, let's be straight, OK?

01:20:01.257 --> 01:20:04.719
You're not some dumb schmuck
up here to snatch a few purses.

01:20:04.802 --> 01:20:06.429
You're very perceptive.

01:20:06.512 --> 01:20:11.017
I watch <i>60 Minutes.</i>
I say to myself, these guys are professional,

01:20:11.100 --> 01:20:13.519
they're motivated, they're happening.

01:20:13.603 --> 01:20:15.188
They want something.

01:20:15.271 --> 01:20:20.401
I couldn't care less about your politics.
Maybe you're pissed off at the camel jockeys.

01:20:20.485 --> 01:20:23.404
Maybe it's Northern Ireland.
It's none of my business.

01:20:23.488 --> 01:20:27.033
- You're here to negotiate, right?
- You're amazing.

01:20:27.116 --> 01:20:29.452
You figured this all out already?

01:20:29.535 --> 01:20:31.662
Hey, business is business.

01:20:31.746 --> 01:20:34.999
You use a gun, I use a fountain pen.
What's the difference?

01:20:35.083 --> 01:20:37.668
In my terms,
you're here on a hostile takeover.

01:20:37.752 --> 01:20:42.298
You grab us for some greenmail but didn't
expect a poison pill to be running around.

01:20:42.382 --> 01:20:43.758
Am I right?

01:20:43.841 --> 01:20:45.385
Hans,

01:20:45.468 --> 01:20:48.805
bubbee, I'm your white knight.

01:20:49.931 --> 01:20:54.811
I must have missed <i>60 Minutes.</i>
What are you saying?

01:20:56.145 --> 01:20:59.357
The guy upstairs
who's fucking things up, huh?

01:21:03.736 --> 01:21:06.489
I can give him to you.

01:21:08.324 --> 01:21:10.451
<i>(McClane) Oh, God...</i>

01:21:12.537 --> 01:21:14.914
Roy? Roy, you all right?

01:21:16.165 --> 01:21:19.419
Just trying to fire down
a 1,000-year-old Twinkie.

01:21:19.502 --> 01:21:20.169
<i>(spits)</i>

01:21:20.211 --> 01:21:21.712
What do they put in them?

01:21:23.172 --> 01:21:27.093
Sugar-enriched flour,
partially hydrogenated vegetable oil,

01:21:27.176 --> 01:21:30.388
polysorbate 60, and yellow dye number five.

01:21:30.471 --> 01:21:33.933
<i>Just everything a growing boy needs.</i>

01:21:34.016 --> 01:21:35.893
How many kids you got, Al?

01:21:35.977 --> 01:21:40.064
<i>As a matter of fact,
my wife is working on our first.</i>

01:21:40.148 --> 01:21:44.360
How about you, cowboy?
You got any kids back on your ranch?

01:21:45.570 --> 01:21:47.280
Yeah.

01:21:47.363 --> 01:21:48.406
Two.

01:21:48.865 --> 01:21:52.952
Sure hope I can see them swinging
on a jungle gym with Al Jr someday.

01:21:53.035 --> 01:21:55.079
<i>(Powell laughs)</i>

01:21:55.455 --> 01:21:59.834
<i>Well, now, that's a date,
but you bring the ice cream.</i>

01:21:59.917 --> 01:22:03.004
<i>(Hans) Touching, cowboy. Touching.</i>

01:22:03.087 --> 01:22:06.591
Or should I call you... Mr McClane?

01:22:07.925 --> 01:22:10.553
Mr Officer John McClane

01:22:10.636 --> 01:22:13.306
of the New York Police Department?

01:22:14.891 --> 01:22:17.143
Get on the phone to Harry in New York.

01:22:17.226 --> 01:22:19.562
Get a hold of somebody at Dispatch.

01:22:19.645 --> 01:22:24.108
Sister Theresa called me
Mr McClane in the third grade.

01:22:24.192 --> 01:22:28.571
My friends call me John,
and you're neither, shithead.

01:22:28.654 --> 01:22:35.161
I have someone who wants to talk to you.
A very special friend

01:22:35.244 --> 01:22:37.830
who was with you at the party tonight.

01:22:43.794 --> 01:22:45.922
Hey, John boy.

01:22:47.215 --> 01:22:48.841
Ellis?

01:22:48.925 --> 01:22:50.259
<i>Yeah.</i>

01:22:50.343 --> 01:22:54.305
<i>Listen, John, they're giving me
a few minutes to talk sense into you.</i>

01:22:54.388 --> 01:22:57.433
I know you think you're doing your job,

01:22:57.517 --> 01:23:00.520
but you're dragging this out.

01:23:00.603 --> 01:23:04.148
No one gets out of here until these guys
can talk to the LA police.

01:23:04.232 --> 01:23:07.652
That won't happen until you stop
messing up the works. <i>Capisce?</i>

01:23:13.199 --> 01:23:14.951
Ellis, what have you told them?

01:23:16.410 --> 01:23:21.624
That we were old friends
and you were my guest at the party.

01:23:21.707 --> 01:23:23.668
Ellis, you shouldn't be doing this.

01:23:23.751 --> 01:23:25.753
Tell me about it.

01:23:31.634 --> 01:23:33.344
All right, John, listen.

01:23:34.387 --> 01:23:36.639
<i>Tell them where the detonators are.</i>

01:23:36.722 --> 01:23:38.975
<i>They know people are listening.</i>

01:23:39.058 --> 01:23:42.979
<i>They want the detonators,
or they're gonna kill me.</i>

01:23:46.524 --> 01:23:47.942
John, didn't you hear me?

01:23:50.403 --> 01:23:52.280
Yeah, I hear you.

01:23:52.363 --> 01:23:56.909
John, get with the programme!
The police are here now. It's their problem.

01:23:56.993 --> 01:23:59.537
Tell them where the detonators are!

01:23:59.620 --> 01:24:02.665
I'm putting my life on the line for you, pal!

01:24:02.748 --> 01:24:04.625
<i>Ellis, listen to me carefully.</i>

01:24:04.709 --> 01:24:05.376
John...

01:24:05.459 --> 01:24:09.630
Shut up, Ellis! Just shut your mouth!
Put Hans back on the line.

01:24:09.714 --> 01:24:14.302
<i>Hans, this shithead doesn't know
what kind of man you are, but I do.</i>

01:24:14.385 --> 01:24:17.847
Then you'll give us what we want
and save your friend's life.

01:24:17.930 --> 01:24:20.141
You're not part of this equation.

01:24:20.224 --> 01:24:22.518
Hey, what am I, a Method actor?

01:24:22.602 --> 01:24:25.938
<i>Babe, put away the gun.
This is radio, not television.</i>

01:24:26.022 --> 01:24:29.650
Hans, this asshole is not my friend!
I don't know him!

01:24:29.734 --> 01:24:34.780
Jesus Christ, Ellis! These people
will kill you! Tell them you don't know me!

01:24:34.864 --> 01:24:37.283
<i>How can you say that after all these years?</i>

01:24:37.366 --> 01:24:41.203
John? John?

01:24:49.295 --> 01:24:50.630
<i>(gunshot)</i>

01:24:50.713 --> 01:24:52.715
<i>(screaming)</i>

01:25:00.806 --> 01:25:03.392
<i>(screaming on radio)</i>

01:25:04.602 --> 01:25:06.437
Do you hear that?

01:25:06.520 --> 01:25:09.315
Talk to me! Where are my detonators?

01:25:09.398 --> 01:25:11.942
Where are they,
or shall I shoot another one?

01:25:12.026 --> 01:25:16.447
<i>Sooner or later,
I might get to someone you do care about.</i>

01:25:16.530 --> 01:25:19.116
Go fuck yourself, Hans.

01:25:20.326 --> 01:25:22.411
He just let the guy die.

01:25:22.495 --> 01:25:26.707
He gave him up. Give me that headset.
That's like pulling the trigger yourself.

01:25:26.791 --> 01:25:30.461
Can't you see what's happening?
Can't you read between the lines?

01:25:30.544 --> 01:25:32.838
He did everything he could to save him.

01:25:32.922 --> 01:25:36.050
If he gave himself up,
they'd both be dead right now!

01:25:36.133 --> 01:25:38.803
No way, man. They'd be talking to us.

01:25:38.886 --> 01:25:42.390
You tell this partner of yours
to stay out of this from now on.

01:25:42.473 --> 01:25:46.018
Because if he doesn't,
I'm really going to nail his ass.

01:25:46.102 --> 01:25:49.271
The man is hurting. He is alone, tired,

01:25:49.355 --> 01:25:53.025
and he hasn't seen diddly-squat
from anybody here!

01:25:53.109 --> 01:25:55.611
You're gonna tell me he'll give a damn

01:25:55.695 --> 01:25:58.864
about what you do to him
if he makes it out of there alive?

01:25:58.948 --> 01:26:01.867
Why don't you wake up
and smell what you shovelling?

01:26:01.951 --> 01:26:03.577
You listen to me, Sergeant.

01:26:03.661 --> 01:26:07.289
Any time you want to go home,
you consider yourself dismissed.

01:26:07.373 --> 01:26:10.584
No, sir. You couldn't drag me away.

01:26:10.960 --> 01:26:13.629
<i>(Hans) Attention, police.</i>

01:26:13.713 --> 01:26:15.798
<i>Attention, police.</i>

01:26:15.881 --> 01:26:19.009
- This is Sergeant Al Powell...
- Give me that.

01:26:19.093 --> 01:26:22.596
This is Deputy Chief Dwayne Robinson.
Who is this?

01:26:22.680 --> 01:26:25.391
This is Hans Gruber.

01:26:25.474 --> 01:26:28.978
I assume you realise the futility
of direct action against me.

01:26:29.061 --> 01:26:30.980
We have no wish for further loss of life.

01:26:31.063 --> 01:26:34.108
What is it you do wish for?

01:26:34.191 --> 01:26:38.446
I have comrades in arms
around the world languishing in prison.

01:26:38.529 --> 01:26:42.199
The American State Department
enjoys rattling its sabre for its own ends.

01:26:42.283 --> 01:26:44.326
Now it can rattle it for me.

01:26:45.745 --> 01:26:49.915
The following people
are to be released from their captors.

01:26:49.999 --> 01:26:53.127
In Northern Ireland,
seven members of the New Provo Front.

01:26:53.210 --> 01:26:57.840
<i>In Canada, the five imprisoned leaders
of Liberté de Quebec.</i>

01:26:57.923 --> 01:27:01.886
<i>In Sri Lanka, the nine members
of the Asian Dawn.</i>

01:27:01.969 --> 01:27:03.471
What the fuck?

01:27:03.554 --> 01:27:05.389
<i>(whispers)</i> Asian Dawn?

01:27:05.473 --> 01:27:07.975
I read about them in <i>Time</i> magazine.

01:27:08.058 --> 01:27:11.979
When these revolutionary
brothers and sisters are free,

01:27:12.062 --> 01:27:15.274
the hostages in this building
will be taken to the roof

01:27:15.357 --> 01:27:20.029
and they will accompany us in helicopters
to LA International Airport

01:27:20.112 --> 01:27:24.700
where they will be given further instructions.
You have two hours to comply.

01:27:24.784 --> 01:27:28.245
Wait a minute. Uh, Mr Gruber. This is crazy.

01:27:28.329 --> 01:27:32.124
I don't have the authority.
Two hours is not enough.

01:27:32.208 --> 01:27:34.502
Hello? Hello!

01:27:36.587 --> 01:27:39.757
Did you get all that?
We got to make some calls.

01:27:39.840 --> 01:27:41.967
Do you think they'll even try?

01:27:42.051 --> 01:27:44.053
Who cares?

01:27:46.472 --> 01:27:48.641
Theo, are we on schedule?

01:27:48.724 --> 01:27:50.643
One more to go, then it's up to you.

01:27:50.726 --> 01:27:54.146
You better be right,
because the last one will take a miracle.

01:27:54.230 --> 01:27:55.815
It's Christmas, Theo.

01:27:55.898 --> 01:27:58.442
It's the time of miracles,
so be of good cheer

01:27:58.526 --> 01:28:01.320
and call me when you hit the last lock.

01:28:02.029 --> 01:28:03.072
Karl,

01:28:03.155 --> 01:28:06.826
hunt that little shit down
and get those detonators.

01:28:06.909 --> 01:28:08.994
Fritz is checking the explosives.

01:28:09.078 --> 01:28:11.789
I'll check the explosives.
You just get the detonators.

01:28:12.748 --> 01:28:14.208
Hey, Powell, you out there?

01:28:15.584 --> 01:28:17.378
I'm here, John. I'm here.

01:28:17.461 --> 01:28:20.965
You gotta believe me.
There was nothing I could do.

01:28:22.299 --> 01:28:25.052
Well, it's gonna be
both our asses if you're wrong.

01:28:25.135 --> 01:28:27.137
I hear you.

01:28:32.601 --> 01:28:35.020
Did you catch that bullshit
Hans was running?

01:28:35.104 --> 01:28:37.648
<i>It doesn't make sense, man.</i>

01:28:38.983 --> 01:28:42.987
Don't ask me. I'm just a desk jockey
who was on my way home when you rang.

01:28:43.070 --> 01:28:46.740
The way you drove that car,
I figured you for the street, Al.

01:28:46.949 --> 01:28:49.618
<i>In my youth. In my youth.</i>

01:28:49.952 --> 01:28:55.040
<i>..and author of "Hostage Terrorist,
Terrorist Hostage: A Study in Duality."</i>

01:28:55.124 --> 01:28:58.669
<i>Dr Hasseldorf, what can we expect
in the next few hours?</i>

01:28:58.752 --> 01:28:59.545
<i>Well, Gail,</i>

01:28:59.628 --> 01:29:04.550
the hostages should be going through
the early stages of the Helsinki Syndrome.

01:29:04.633 --> 01:29:06.510
As in Helsinki, Sweden.

01:29:06.594 --> 01:29:08.178
<i>(Hasseldorf)</i> Finland.

01:29:08.262 --> 01:29:11.891
Basically, it's when the hostages
and the terrorists

01:29:11.974 --> 01:29:16.812
go through a psychological transference
and a projection of dependency.

01:29:16.896 --> 01:29:19.732
<i>A strange sort of trust and bond develops.</i>

01:29:19.815 --> 01:29:24.820
<i>We've had situations where the hostages
have embraced their captors after release</i>

01:29:24.904 --> 01:29:27.114
<i>and even corresponded with them in prison.</i>

01:29:27.448 --> 01:29:30.242
No, no, darling. Asian Dawn. Dawn.

01:29:30.326 --> 01:29:33.245
D-a-w-n.

01:29:33.329 --> 01:29:34.830
- Sir?
- Yeah?

01:29:34.914 --> 01:29:36.832
Sir, the FBI is here.

01:29:36.916 --> 01:29:40.711
- The FBI is here now?
- Yes, sir. Right over there.

01:29:40.794 --> 01:29:42.129
Hold this.

01:29:42.212 --> 01:29:44.465
Want a breath mint?

01:29:48.469 --> 01:29:50.846
How you doin', man?

01:29:50.930 --> 01:29:53.557
I'm Agent Johnson.
This is Special Agent Johnson.

01:29:53.641 --> 01:29:56.977
- Oh, how you doing?
- No relation.

01:29:57.061 --> 01:29:58.395
I'm, uh...

01:29:59.813 --> 01:30:03.651
I'm Dwayne Robinson, LAPD.
I'm in charge here.

01:30:03.734 --> 01:30:05.778
Not any more.

01:31:00.541 --> 01:31:04.086
Hi, there. How you doing?

01:31:07.423 --> 01:31:08.424
Ohh...

01:31:10.050 --> 01:31:13.220
Please, God. No.
You're one of them, aren't you?

01:31:13.303 --> 01:31:14.805
You're one of them.

01:31:14.888 --> 01:31:17.766
No! Don't kill me! Please!

01:31:17.850 --> 01:31:20.310
Don't kill me, please! Please, please!

01:31:20.394 --> 01:31:23.188
Whoa. Relax. I'm not gonna hurt you.

01:31:23.272 --> 01:31:24.940
I'm not gonna hurt you!

01:31:27.484 --> 01:31:29.111
Oh, God.

01:31:32.573 --> 01:31:35.784
What are you doin' up here?
What were you lookin' for?

01:31:35.868 --> 01:31:38.287
I managed to get out of there and...

01:31:38.370 --> 01:31:41.498
I was just trying to get up on the roof...

01:31:41.582 --> 01:31:44.293
and see if I could signal for help.

01:31:45.794 --> 01:31:47.921
It's through here. Come and help.

01:31:48.005 --> 01:31:51.133
Hold it. Forget the roof.

01:31:51.842 --> 01:31:54.678
Forget the roof. They got people all over it.

01:31:56.096 --> 01:31:58.557
You wanna stay alive, you stay with me.

01:32:01.393 --> 01:32:03.479
The best we can figure it,

01:32:03.562 --> 01:32:07.066
we've got maybe 30 or 35 hostages up there,

01:32:07.149 --> 01:32:09.068
probably on the 30th floor,

01:32:09.151 --> 01:32:12.780
and maybe seven or eight
terrorists up there.

01:32:12.863 --> 01:32:15.032
Sounds like an A-7 scenario.

01:32:15.115 --> 01:32:17.534
Thank you. We'll handle it from here.

01:32:17.618 --> 01:32:20.412
When we commandeer your men,
we'll try and let you know.

01:32:20.496 --> 01:32:23.582
- Aren't you forgetting something?
- Such as?

01:32:23.665 --> 01:32:28.545
What about John McClane?
He's the reason we have any information.

01:32:28.629 --> 01:32:32.257
He's also the reason
you're facing seven terrorists, not twelve.

01:32:32.341 --> 01:32:34.676
He's inside? Who is he?

01:32:34.760 --> 01:32:37.679
He might be a cop. We're checking on that.

01:32:37.763 --> 01:32:40.432
- One of yours?
- No, no way.

01:32:45.979 --> 01:32:46.814
You smoke?

01:32:48.357 --> 01:32:49.858
Yeah.

01:32:54.571 --> 01:32:55.781
Thanks.

01:32:59.660 --> 01:33:02.538
You don't work for Nakatomi.

01:33:06.834 --> 01:33:09.711
And if you're not one of them...

01:33:11.797 --> 01:33:14.258
I'm a cop from New York.

01:33:15.134 --> 01:33:16.718
New York?

01:33:16.802 --> 01:33:18.720
Yeah.

01:33:18.804 --> 01:33:21.640
Got invited to
the Christmas party by mistake.

01:33:21.723 --> 01:33:23.016
Who knew?

01:33:31.650 --> 01:33:35.696
Better than being caught
with your pants down, huh?

01:33:43.036 --> 01:33:45.747
I'm John McClane.

01:33:45.831 --> 01:33:47.332
You're, uh...

01:33:48.709 --> 01:33:50.377
Clay.

01:33:52.337 --> 01:33:53.672
Bill Clay.

01:33:59.761 --> 01:34:01.889
Know how to use a handgun, Bill?

01:34:03.265 --> 01:34:07.644
I spent a weekend at a combat ranch.
That game with the guns that shoot red paint.

01:34:07.728 --> 01:34:09.980
Probably seems stupid to you.

01:34:11.398 --> 01:34:12.608
Nope.

01:34:15.694 --> 01:34:18.530
Time for the real thing, Bill.

01:34:26.038 --> 01:34:28.916
All you got to do is pull the trigger.

01:34:28.999 --> 01:34:29.583
Come on.

01:34:37.925 --> 01:34:42.304
<i>33. Stockwerk. Kommt sofort.</i>

01:34:42.387 --> 01:34:44.389
<i>(gun clicks)</i>

01:34:49.019 --> 01:34:53.315
Put down the gun
and give me my detonators.

01:34:57.778 --> 01:34:59.780
Well, well, well.

01:35:01.156 --> 01:35:02.199
Hans.

01:35:03.242 --> 01:35:05.786
Put it down now.

01:35:09.373 --> 01:35:12.876
That's pretty tricky with that accent.

01:35:12.960 --> 01:35:16.171
You oughta be on fuckin' TV with that accent.

01:35:18.465 --> 01:35:22.094
But what do you want with the detonators?

01:35:22.177 --> 01:35:24.846
I already used all the explosives.

01:35:27.182 --> 01:35:29.893
