02:01:27.074 --> 02:01:31.829
<i>(Hans)</i> Oh, yes. What was it
you said to me before?

02:01:31.912 --> 02:01:35.707
Yippee-ki-yay, motherfucker.

02:01:56.770 --> 02:01:57.771
Holly!

02:02:03.360 --> 02:02:04.862
Happy trails, Hans.

02:02:10.367 --> 02:02:11.994
Aah!

02:02:12.077 --> 02:02:13.912
<i>(Holly screams)</i>

02:02:49.531 --> 02:02:51.408
I hope that's not a hostage.

02:03:15.933 --> 02:03:18.101
<i>(sirens)</i>

02:03:19.811 --> 02:03:23.815
Gimme water hook-ups
for engine companies 5, 3, 9, 6.

02:03:27.486 --> 02:03:29.571
Over here. It's a better angle.

02:03:31.198 --> 02:03:32.491
<i>(horn honks)</i>

02:03:33.784 --> 02:03:36.828
Keep it going, now. Keep it going.

02:03:41.875 --> 02:03:45.504
- Come on. We're going to miss it!
- OK. Hand me my notes!

02:04:08.527 --> 02:04:12.614
What was it like in there?
How did they treat you?

02:04:58.827 --> 02:05:02.581
Al, this is my wife Holly. Holly Gennero.

02:05:03.331 --> 02:05:05.083
Holly McClane.

02:05:05.167 --> 02:05:06.835
Hello, Holly.

02:05:06.918 --> 02:05:11.548
You got yourself a good man.
You take good care of him.

02:05:11.631 --> 02:05:12.966
<i>(Robinson)</i> McClane!

02:05:13.341 --> 02:05:15.886
McClane, I want a debriefing!

02:05:15.969 --> 02:05:18.680
You got some things to answer for, mister.

02:05:18.764 --> 02:05:24.394
Ellis' murder, for one thing. Property damage,
interfering with police business.

02:05:24.478 --> 02:05:26.021
<i>(screaming)</i>

02:06:04.726 --> 02:06:07.813
<i>(Robinson)</i> Go inside,
see if there's anybody else!

02:06:18.532 --> 02:06:21.159
No. This one's with me.

02:06:29.126 --> 02:06:30.460
<i>(horn honks)</i>

02:06:31.044 --> 02:06:32.712
Mr McClane, Mr McClane!

02:06:32.796 --> 02:06:37.717
Now that it's all over and after this
incredible ordeal, what are your feelings?

02:06:39.427 --> 02:06:41.388
<i>(laughter)</i>

02:06:42.639 --> 02:06:44.057
Well, well, well.

02:06:44.141 --> 02:06:48.395
- Merry Christmas, Argyle.
- Merry Christmas.

02:06:51.940 --> 02:06:52.983
<i>Did you get that?</i>

02:06:55.569 --> 02:07:00.407
If this is their idea of Christmas,
I gotta be here for New Year's.

02:07:04.911 --> 02:07:08.498
<i>♪ Oh, the weather outside is frightful</i>

02:07:08.582 --> 02:07:12.377
<i>♪ But the fire is so delightful</i>

02:07:12.460 --> 02:07:15.839
<i>♪ And since we've no place to go</i>

02:07:15.922 --> 02:07:18.925
<i>♪ Let it snow, let it snow, let it snow</i>

02:07:20.260 --> 02:07:23.346
<i>♪ It doesn't show signs of stopping</i>

02:07:23.430 --> 02:07:27.475
<i>♪ And I brought some corn for popping</i>

02:07:27.559 --> 02:07:30.937
<i>♪ The lights are turned way down low</i>

02:07:31.021 --> 02:07:34.608
<i>♪ Let it snow, let it snow, let it snow</i>

02:07:35.066 --> 02:07:38.403
<i>♪ When we finally kiss goodnight</i>

02:07:38.486 --> 02:07:42.574
<i>♪ How I hate goin' out in the storm</i>

02:07:42.657 --> 02:07:46.745
<i>♪ But if you really hold me tight</i>

02:07:46.828 --> 02:07:49.664
<i>♪ All the way home, I'll be warm</i>

02:07:50.290 --> 02:07:53.668
<i>♪ The fire is slowly dying</i>

02:07:53.752 --> 02:07:57.631
<i>♪ And, my dear, we're still good-byeing</i>

02:07:57.714 --> 02:08:01.009
<i>♪ But as long as you love me so</i>

02:08:01.092 --> 02:08:03.303
<i>♪ Let it snow</i>

02:08:03.553 --> 02:08:05.222
<i>♪ Let it snow</i>

02:08:05.472 --> 02:08:10.268
<i>♪ Let it snow</i>
